<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 73, 393, 92]]<|/det|>
The polynomial \(\mathrm{p}(x)\) is defined by

<|ref|>equation<|/ref|><|det|>[[393, 100, 603, 120]]<|/det|>
\[\mathrm{p}(x) = x^{3} + a x^{2} + b x + 16,\]

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 127, 920, 163]]<|/det|>
where \(a\) and \(b\) are constants. It is given that \((x + 2)\) is a factor of \(\mathrm{p}(x)\) and that the remainder is 72 when \(\mathrm{p}(x)\) is divided by \((x - 2)\).

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 173, 332, 191]]<|/det|>
Find the values of \(a\) and \(b\).

<|ref|>text<|/ref|><|det|>[[118, 390, 443, 408]]<|/det|>
